  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "description": {
        "text": "Large, steep granite crag. All the routes are bolted. The rock is more compact than on the MTV wall at Niemisel, and stays dry even after a light shower. Away from the routes, or on routes that are rarely climbed, there can be quite a lot of loose rock.\n\nThe information on Sverigeföraren is all you need to find your way around the crag. All route names are painted on the rock, and there is often a small topo showing the line of the routes.",
        "method": "llm",
        "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
        "sourceIds": [
          "legacy:kallsberget-norrbotten"
        ]
      },
      "sections": {
        "allmant": {
          "title": {
            "text": "General",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kallsberget-norrbotten"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "A large, steep granite crag with bolted routes only. The rock is more compact than on the MTV wall at Niemisel and stays dry even after a brief shower. Away from the established lines, or on routes that are rarely climbed, there can be quite a lot of loose rock.\n\nIt is very easy to find your way around the crag using only the information from Sverigeföraren. All route names are painted on the rock, often accompanied by a small topo showing the line.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kallsberget-norrbotten"
            ]
          }
        },
        "camping": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Camping",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kallsberget-norrbotten"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "You can camp by the crag, but there is no water. The crag is only a minute from the road, so carrying your gear in is no problem. Cabins are also available to rent in Älvsyn.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kallsberget-norrbotten"
            ]
          }
        },
        "annan-klattring-i-narheten": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Other climbing nearby",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kallsberget-norrbotten"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Hundberget is only a few kilometres away and offers a completely different style of sport climbing from Källsberget. Dödlarsberget is about 25 km further inland and has both some easier sport climbing and plenty of trad routes. Lots of quality packed into a small area! Niemisel, one of Sweden’s best sport-climbing crags, lies 80 km to the north.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kallsberget-norrbotten"
            ]
          }
        },
        "vagbeskrivning": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Directions",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kallsberget-norrbotten"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "From the Älvsby crossroads (Piteå–Boden–Vidsel–Älvsbyn), head towards the village. After crossing a bridge, turn left. After about 2 km, the road bends sharply right. Continue for about 1 km and park below the crag.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kallsberget-norrbotten"
            ]
          }
        },
        "leder": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Routes",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kallsberget-norrbotten"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Most of the routes are on the steepest part of the crag. Routes 1 to 3 are further up to the left. The route names are painted on the rock at the starts. The routes are described from the west, moving right.\n\nThese two routes are 150 metres left of the main crag:",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kallsberget-norrbotten"
            ]
          }
        },
        "forare": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Guide",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kallsberget-norrbotten"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "http://www.borrbult.nu\n\nIn English: Long, pumpy routes on overhanging granite. Some loose rock, especially away from established routes.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kallsberget-norrbotten"
            ]
          }
        },
        "directions": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Directions",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kallsberget-norrbotten"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Assuming you are driving to Älvsbyn from the coast, turn left immediately after the bridge over the river. Follow the sign for Motorstadion. Continue along the road towards Sikfors for 5–6 km. Pass under a railway bridge and the wall will appear on your right. Park on the short dirt road on the right, about 200 m after the bridge, and follow the road/trail for 100 m.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:kallsberget-norrbotten"
            ]
          }
        },
        "staying-there": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Staying there",
